.SH NAME
vmw_kms_update_proxy \- Helper function to update a proxy surface from its backing MOB.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vmw_kms_update_proxy
.BI "(struct vmw_resource *res "  ","
.BI "const struct drm_clip_rect *clips "  ","
.BI "unsigned num_clips "  ","
.BI "int increment "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "res" 12
Pointer to the surface resource
.IP "clips" 12
Clip rects in framebuffer (surface) space.
.IP "num_clips" 12
Number of clips in \fIclips\fP.
.IP "increment" 12
Integer with which to increment the clip counter when looping.
Used to skip a predetermined number of clip rects.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function makes sure the proxy surface is updated from its backing MOB
using the region given by \fIclips\fP. The surface resource \fIres\fP and its backing
MOB needs to be reserved and validated on call.
